Transcription.Text: As they required greater precision in manufacture than the beam-scales, few home-made examples survive. Graduation marks are provided by brass pegs driven into the wood at regular intervals. An example of a craftsman-made wooden steelyard can be seen in the illustration of the fine Orkney pundler, whith is one of the prized exhibits in the collection.
